## üß≠ RECURSION ROADMAP (From Beginner ‚Üí Advanced)

> Covers all key recursion patterns asked in FAANG / Product-based interviews.

---

### üß© **Stage 1: Basics ‚Äî Build the Foundation**

Learn how recursion *works* (base case, recursive calls, stack flow).
‚è± Focus: Understanding the flow, tracing recursion tree.

| # | Problem                                               | Concept                    | Company Tags     |
| - | ----------------------------------------------------- | -------------------------- | ---------------- |
| 1 | Print numbers from 1 to N (both ascending/descending) | Simple base case recursion | Amazon, TCS      |
| 2 | Sum of first N numbers                                | Return-based recursion     | Accenture        |
| 3 | Factorial of N                                        | Basic recursion            | Infosys, Wipro   |
| 4 | Fibonacci series (recursive)                          | Overlapping subproblems    | Amazon           |
| 5 | Reverse a string / array recursively                  | Recursion on indices       | Google, Flipkart |
| 6 | Check palindrome string recursively                   | Two-pointer recursion      | Zoho             |
| 7 | Find maximum element in array recursively             | Divide into smaller arrays | HCL 
If you want, your next recursion problems can be:

Reverse an array using recursion

Check if a string is palindrome

Sum of digits using recursion

Count digits

Print array in reverse order             |

üéØ **Goal:** Be 100% comfortable tracing function calls and understanding the recursion stack.

---

### üß© **Stage 2: Intermediate ‚Äî Problem Solving Using Recursion**

Learn recursion with arrays, strings, and multiple branches.

| # | Problem                                                 | Concept                     | Company Tags  |
| - | ------------------------------------------------------- | --------------------------- | ------------- |
| 1 | Print all subsequences of a string/array                | Pick / Not-pick pattern     | Amazon, Adobe |
| 2 | Power of a number (`x^n`) using recursion               | Divide & conquer            | Google        |
| 3 | Binary Search using recursion                           | Mid recursion logic         | Microsoft     |
| 4 | Tower of Hanoi                                          | Classic recursion pattern   | Amazon        |
| 5 | Generate binary strings of length N                     | Constraints with recursion  | PayPal        |
| 6 | Generate all valid parentheses                          | Recursion + condition-based | Facebook      |
| 7 | Find all subsets of a given array                       | Power set                   | Amazon        |
| 8 | Count total paths in a matrix (right & down moves only) | 2D recursion                | Flipkart      |

üéØ **Goal:** Understand recursion trees, branching factor, and how recursion explores all paths.

---

### üß© **Stage 3: Backtracking ‚Äî Recursion with Constraints**

Now recursion + decision-making (undo step ‚Üí backtrack).

| # | Problem                               | Concept                               | Company Tags      |
| - | ------------------------------------- | ------------------------------------- | ----------------- |
| 1 | Rat in a Maze                         | Backtracking pathfinding              | Amazon            |
| 2 | N-Queens Problem                      | Recursion + backtrack on board        | Google, Microsoft |
| 3 | Sudoku Solver                         | Classic backtracking                  | Adobe, Samsung    |
| 4 | Word Search in a Grid                 | Recursion + DFS                       | Amazon            |
| 5 | Permutations of a String              | Swap / fix + recursive                | Flipkart          |
| 6 | Combination Sum (I & II)              | Subset + backtrack with sum condition | Google, Meta      |
| 7 | Subset Sum Problem                    | Recursion + pruning                   | Paytm             |
| 8 | Letter Combinations of a Phone Number | Recursive digit mapping               | Amazon            |

üéØ **Goal:** Learn how to ‚Äúexplore ‚Üí backtrack ‚Üí try next option‚Äù ‚Äî core skill for advanced recursion.

---

### üß© **Stage 4: Advanced ‚Äî Recursion to DP Transition**

Here recursion becomes inefficient ‚Üí you optimize using **memoization / tabulation**.

| # | Problem                              | DP Transition Type      | Company Tags |
| - | ------------------------------------ | ----------------------- | ------------ |
| 1 | Fibonacci ‚Üí Memoization ‚Üí Tabulation | 1D DP base case         | Google       |
| 2 | Climbing Stairs                      | DP on recursion         | Amazon       |
| 3 | Grid Unique Paths                    | 2D recursion ‚Üí DP       | Microsoft    |
| 4 | Subset Sum ‚Üí Memoization             | Boolean DP              | Adobe        |
| 5 | 0/1 Knapsack                         | Recursion + Memoization | Amazon       |
| 6 | Longest Common Subsequence           | DP from recursion       | Google       |
| 7 | Partition Equal Subset Sum           | DP recursion            | Facebook     |
| 8 | Minimum Path Sum in a Grid           | Recursive ‚Üí Tabulation  | Flipkart     |

üéØ **Goal:** Be able to convert recursive problems into efficient DP solutions.

---

### üß© **Stage 5: Expert-Level / Recursion + Patterns**

These are mixed recursion + other DSA ‚Äî asked in product companies.

| # | Problem                                 | Type                       | Company Tags |
| - | --------------------------------------- | -------------------------- | ------------ |
| 1 | All Paths from Source to Target (Graph) | DFS Recursion              | Google       |
| 2 | Word Break Problem                      | Recursion + DP             | Amazon       |
| 3 | Palindrome Partitioning                 | Recursion + Backtracking   | Microsoft    |
| 4 | Restore IP Addresses                    | Recursive String Splitting | Meta         |
| 5 | Combination Sum IV                      | Recursion + DP             | Google       |
| 6 | Generate Binary Tree from Traversals    | Recursive Tree Building    | Adobe        |
| 7 | Serialize and Deserialize Binary Tree   | Recursion                  | Google       |

üéØ **Goal:** Recursion applied to **real interview-level mixed problems**.

